transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm going to use your telephone number, Bruce, to pull up your account.

Speaker 2: I'm going to read off the chart, Bruce, and I'm going to help you put a stop to this.

Speaker 1: All right, bud?

Speaker 2: Just bear with me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much, bud.

Speaker 2: So when I do pull up your chart, just correct me if I'm wrong so I can verify some things.

Speaker 1: First, you're working with one of our Pfizer doctors, Dr. Michael Chu, and it looks like—

Speaker 2: Dr. Chu set you up with a VIP status and he wrote a script for 50 milligrams of the—

Speaker 1: White diamond pill that we make in our Pfizer lab, it's the FDA approved one, it's the Viagra—

Speaker 2: The Pfizer Viagra.

Speaker 1: And I do see that Dr. Chu has ordered the pharmacy to send you refills on his behalf—

Speaker 2: On a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: Do you want me to put a stop to that so you're not getting them?

Speaker 2: I don't want any refills.

Speaker 1: I don't want any refills.

Speaker 2: Stop them all.

Speaker 1: Stop them all.

Speaker 2: I completely understand.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I completely understand, man.

Speaker 2: That really grinds my gears.

Speaker 1: I assume they probably weren't working for you.

Speaker 2: Whatever he wrote on the script wasn't working for you because if you got three of them and—

Speaker 1: Refills and they weren't working, I'd be pissed off too.

Speaker 2: So just hold your line and I'll put a stop to this, bud.

Speaker 1: All right?

Speaker 2: One moment.

Speaker 1: Yes, please do that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you got it, Bruce.

Speaker 1: We got you back.

Speaker 2: One moment.
